AddThoughts: A large portion of my friends, me included, aren't happy here. It is a really hard place to balance school and athletics and truly be successful at both. Both activities take such a large portion of the day that one can truly only focus on one activity in order to just survive in it. This will take away either from academic success or from athletic success which doesn't help ones mental state. The administration often talks about the stat that 45% of the student body talks to counseling. The manner in which they talk about this is often prideful and they don't seem to see an issue. I know plenty of people who could use counseling but don't. I think there is a bigger issue at hand considering 45% of the student body (I think the number could be higher) talks to counseling at Choate due to anxiety and depression. The fact that I had never had any issues regarding depression or anxiety before my time at Choate says something about the school.
